\sum_{k=0}^n \binom{2n+1}{2k+1} = 4^{n}
\binom{2n}{2k}+\binom{2n}{2k+1}=\binom{2n+1}{2k+1}
\binom{2n}{2n}=1=\binom{2n+1}{2n+1}
4^n=(1+1)^{2n}=\sum_{k=0}^{2n}\binom{2n}k=\sum_{k=0}^n\binom{2n+1}{2k+1}
